abstract: World Wildlife Fund says that number of Monarch butterflies that successfully migrated to Mexico for winter has rebounded 69 percent from extremely low levels reported in 2014, but are still nowhere near their peak in 1996.
lead_paragraph: The number of Monarch butterflies that reached wintering grounds in Mexico rebounded 69 percent this year from last year’s disastrous levels, the World Wildlife Fund said.
